\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.4}{\ignorespaces FPR Comparison: Global vs. 4D Context-Aware Thresholds. Global thresholds catastrophically fail on airport trips (51.2\% FPR for JFK, 68.9\% for Newark), while 4D context-aware thresholds reduce FPR to below 6\% across all contexts. The bar chart shows the 9.2$\times $ FPR reduction (38.7\% $\to $ 4.2\%) achieved by context-aware thresholding over global thresholds. The weighted average FPR reduction accounting for class imbalance across 4 trip type categories is 4.9$\times $, reflecting the higher FPR rates in rare special ratecode categories.}}{44}{figure.caption.31}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:exp5a_fpr_comparison}{{6.4}{44}{FPR Comparison: Global vs. 4D Context-Aware Thresholds. Global thresholds catastrophically fail on airport trips (51.2\% FPR for JFK, 68.9\% for Newark), while 4D context-aware thresholds reduce FPR to below 6\% across all contexts. The bar chart shows the 9.2$\times $ FPR reduction (38.7\% $\to $ 4.2\%) achieved by context-aware thresholding over global thresholds. The weighted average FPR reduction accounting for class imbalance across 4 trip type categories is 4.9$\times $, reflecting the higher FPR rates in rare special ratecode categories}{figure.caption.31}{}}
